Package: tidywoe
Title: A tidy way to put WoE version of categorical variables in data.frame.
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: person("Athos", "Damiani", email = "athos.damiani@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: This package provide a easy way to put WoE (Weight of Evidence) in a data.frame, frequently used when modeling using Logistic Regression.
Depends: R (>= 3.4.0)
License: MIT license
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Imports: dplyr,
    magrittr,
    tibble,
    tidyr
Suggests: testthat
